113.8	The_Rocky_Horror_Picture_Show	The Rocky Horror Picture Show	The Rocky Horror Picture Show is the 1975 film adaptation of the British rock musical stageplay, The Rocky Horror Show, written by Richard O'Brien. The film is a parody of B-movie, science fiction and horror films of the late 1940s through early 1970s. Director Jim Sharman collaborated on the screenplay with O'Brien, who wrote both the book and lyrics for the stage. The film introduces Tim Curry and features Susan Sarandon and Barry Bostwick along with cast members from the original Kings Road production presented at the Royal Court Theatre, London, in 1973.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/The_Rocky_Horror_Picture_Show.jpg/220px-The_Rocky_Horror_Picture_Show.jpg
